-{"id":"bd-3uqs","title":"Shared SSH Command Execution Infrastructure","description":"## Overview
Create robust, reusable SSH command execution utilities that all fleet operations depend on.
This is foundational infrastructure that run_preflight(), get_fleet_status(), and rollback_workers()
will all leverage.

## Background & Motivation
Currently executor.rs has working SSH/SCP helpers (test_ssh_connectivity, create_remote_directory,
copy_binary_via_scp, etc.) but they're tightly coupled to deployment operations. We need more
general-purpose SSH utilities that can:
- Execute arbitrary commands with structured output
- Handle timeouts gracefully without hanging
- Parse command output reliably
- Support both synchronous results and streaming output
- Provide consistent error handling across all fleet operations

## Technical Requirements

### 1. Core SSH Executor
\`\`\`rust
pub struct SshExecutor {
    worker: WorkerConfig,
    timeout: Duration,
    connect_timeout: Duration,
}

impl SshExecutor {
    pub async fn run_command(&self, cmd: &str) -> Result<CommandOutput, FleetError>;
    pub async fn run_command_raw(&self, cmd: &str) -> Result<String, FleetError>;
    pub async fn check_connectivity(&self) -> Result<bool, FleetError>;
}

pub struct CommandOutput {
    pub stdout: String,
    pub stderr: String,
    pub exit_code: i32,
    pub duration: Duration,
}
\`\`\`

### 2. SSH Options Builder
Consistent SSH options across all operations:
- StrictHostKeyChecking configuration (from WorkerConfig)
- ConnectTimeout (default: 10s)
- ServerAliveInterval / ServerAliveCountMax for long operations
- BatchMode=yes for non-interactive execution
- IdentityFile support
- ProxyJump/ProxyCommand support (from WorkerConfig)

### 3. Error Handling
Create specific error variants:
- ConnectionTimeout: SSH connection couldn't be established
- CommandTimeout: Command started but didn't complete in time
- AuthenticationFailed: Key/password rejected
- HostUnreachable: Network-level failure
- CommandFailed { exit_code, stderr }: Command ran but failed

### 4. Output Parsing Utilities
\`\`\`rust
pub fn parse_disk_space(df_output: &str) -> Result<DiskInfo, ParseError>;
pub fn parse_load_average(uptime_output: &str) -> Result<LoadInfo, ParseError>;
pub fn parse_version_string(version_output: &str) -> Result<Version, ParseError>;
\`\`\`

